The paper deals with pedestrian trajectory prediction in crowd scenarios, which is a problem in computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO). The proposed method is based on LSTM networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG) research. The paper also introduces a social-aware information selection mechanism, which involves attention mechanisms that are often used in machine learning and signal processing (SI) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, and cs.SI.
